title: Trump generated 'more than $100m' through fraud,  court hears
description: Donald Trump is accused of raising more than $100m by lying about the value of his real estate empire, as he attacked the judge overseeing his civil fraud trial.

title: Planets floating in pairs without star to orbit found in surprise discovery
description: Scientists say they have discovered planet-like objects in a distant nebula unconnected to any star to orbit - and floating in pairs.

title: First-ever space debris fine issued
description: A company has been fined by the US government for leaving junk in space.

title: Apple says it will fix issue causing iPhone 15 to get too hot - and blames some apps for 'overloading the system'
description: Apple is blaming a software bug and issues tied to apps like Instagram and Uber for causing its recently released iPhone 15 models to get too hot.

title: Cheap malaria vaccine approved for global rollout
description: The World Health Organisation (WHO) has approved a low-cost, readily available vaccine for malaria that promises to help ease one of the greatest disease burdens on the developing world.

title: UEFA vice president 'sorry' after voting for Russia's football return
description: The second in command at European football's governing body has apologised after Sky News revealed how he voted to end a blanket ban on Russia's teams competing in continental competitions - contradicting the strong stance of the Swedish sports body he leads.

title: 'Something's not right': Family seeks answers after British man's death in Vietnam
description: The family of a British man have said "we don't know what to believe" over the circumstances of his death during a holiday in Vietnam.

title: Thousands of fish and 100 dolphins dead as Amazon water hits record-breaking temperatures
description: More than 100 dolphins and thousands of fish have been found dead in the Brazilian Amazon as drought and record-breaking high temperatures grip the region.

title: 'Groundbreaking' COVID vaccine scientists win Nobel Prize in medicine
description: The Nobel Prize in medicine has been awarded to two scientists for their research which led to the development of effective mRNA vaccines against COVID-19.

title: Sagrada Familia nears completion as towers are crowned
description: More than 140 years since work began on Barcelona's famous Sagrada Familia (The Holy Family) the city is celebrating a milestone: the completion of four of its towers.

title: UK hands £4bn contract to BAE for 'powerful attack' submarines
description: Britain has awarded BAE Systems a £4bn contract to build "powerful attack" submarines as part of the AUKUS security pact with the US and Australia.

title: Simone Biles breaks record at first world championships after two years away over mental health
description: US gymnast Simone Biles became the first woman to land a Yurchenko double pike vault when she competed internationally for the first time in two years on Sunday.

title: Gerard Depardieu writes open letter to deny rape claims
description: Actor Gerard Depardieu has written an open letter to deny claims of rape and sexual assault.

title: What are Donald Trump's biggest assets and how much does he claim they are worth?
description: Donald Trump could be fined $250m (£201.3m) and banned from owning real estate in New York for five years after a judge ruled that he and his associates inflated their assets by as much as $3.6bn (£2.9bn).

title: At least nine dead - including children - after church roof collapses
description: At least nine people - including three children - have been killed and dozens remain trapped after the roof of a church came crashing down during Sunday mass in northern Mexico.

title: Donald Trump's fraud trial is about to start - but he argues his rivals are 'out to get him'
description: Donald Trump has hinted that he will make a surprise appearance on the first day of his trial for "astounding" fraud which begins in New York today.
